  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  impaired left ventricular function (Ejection Fraction &lt; 30%)

          -  large area of myocardium at risk (BCIS-1 Myocardial Jeopardy Score â‰¥ 8/12)

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  cardiogenic shock

          -  acute STEMI within previous 48 hours

          -  complications of recent AMI (including ventricular septal defect, severe mitral
             regurgitation, intractable ventricular arrhythmias)

          -  contraindications to IABP use (including significant iliac or femoral arterial disease
             and more than mild aortic regurgitation)
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
